______________________________________

Mounting a Volume 
To mount a data volume to a container add the --mount or -v flag to the docker run command. It adds the volume to the specified container, where it stores the data produced inside the virtual environment. 
docker run -it --name=srv01 --mount source=testvol1,destination=/data centos
docker run -it --name srv03 -v testvol1:/data centos

To give another container access to a container's volumes, we can provide the --volumes-from argument to docker run. For example: 
docker run -it --volumes-from srv01 --name srv02 centos /bin/bash

or we can use following commands as well.

docker run -it --name srv02 --mount source=testvol1,destination=/data centos
docker run -it --name srv03 -v testvol1:/data centos

